msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:34
msgid "The minimum PHP version for DokuWiki is now 7.2, which is exactly what Rocky Linux 8 comes with. Rocky Linux 9.0 comes with PHP version 8.0, which is also fully supported. We are specifying packages here that may already be installed:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:36
msgid "`dnf install tar wget httpd php php-gd php-xml php-json php-mbstring`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:38
msgid "You will see a list of additional dependencies that will be installed and this prompt:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:40
msgid "`Is this ok [y/N]:`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:42
msgid "Go ahead and answer with \"y\" and hit 'Enter' to install."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:43
#, no-wrap
msgid "Create Directories And Modify Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:45
#, no-wrap
msgid "Apache Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:48
msgid "If you have read through the [Apache Sites Enabled](../web/apache-sites-enabled.md) procedure, you know that we need to create a few directories. We will start with the _httpd_ configuration directory additions:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:50
msgid "`mkdir -p /etc/httpd/{sites-available,sites-enabled}`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:52
msgid "We need to edit the httpd.conf file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:54
msgid "`vi /etc/httpd/conf/httpd.conf`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:56
msgid "And add this to the very bottom of the file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:58
msgid "`Include /etc/httpd/sites-enabled`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:60
msgid "Create the site configuration file in sites-available:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:62
msgid "`vi /etc/httpd/sites-available/com.example`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:64
msgid "That configuration file should look something like this:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:65
#, no-wrap
msgid "<VirtualHost *>\n"
"\tServerName    example.com\n"
"\tDocumentRoot  /var/www/sub-domains/com.example/html\n\n"
"\t<Directory ~ \"/var/www/sub-domains/com.example/html/(bin/|conf/|data/|inc/)\">\n"
"\t    <IfModule mod_authz_core.c>\n"
"                AllowOverride All\n"
"        \tRequire all denied\n"
"\t    </IfModule>\n"
"\t    <IfModule !mod_authz_core.c>\n"
"\t        Order allow,deny\n"
"        \tDeny from all\n"
"\t    </IfModule>\n"
"\t</Directory>\n\n"
"\tErrorLog   /var/log/httpd/example.com_error.log\n"
"\tCustomLog  /var/log/httpd/example.com_access.log combined\n"
"</VirtualHost>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:87
msgid "Note that the \"AllowOverride All\" above, allows the .htaccess (directory specific security) file to work."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:89
msgid "Go ahead and link the configuration file into sites-enabled, but don't start web services as yet:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:91
msgid "`ln -s /etc/httpd/sites-available/com.example /etc/httpd/sites-enabled/`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:92
#, no-wrap
msgid "Apache DocumentRoot"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:95
msgid "We also need to create our _DocumentRoot_. To do this:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:97
msgid "`mkdir -p /var/www/sub-domains/com.example/html`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:98
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing DokuWiki"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:101
msgid "In your server, change to the root directory."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:103
msgid "`cd /root`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:105
msgid "Now that we have our environment ready to go, let's get the latest stable version of DokuWiki. You can find this by going to [the download page](https://download.dokuwiki.org/) and on the left-hand side of the page under \"Version\" you will see \"Stable (Recommended) (direct link).\""
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:107
msgid "Right-click on the \"(direct link)\" portion of this and copy the link address. In the console of your DokuWiki server, type \"wget\" and a space and then paste in your copied link in the terminal. You should get something like this:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:109
msgid "`wget https://download.dokuwiki.org/src/dokuwiki/dokuwiki-stable.tgz`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:111
msgid "Before we decompress the archive, take a look at the contents using `tar ztf` to see the contents of the archive:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:113
msgid "`tar ztvf dokuwiki-stable.tgz`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:115
msgid "Notice the named dated directory ahead of all the other files that looks something like this?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:116
